            <title>[GROOVY-1852] Closure constant on interface not callable without call()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1852</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I add a closure constant in an interface, I can&apos;t call it with V.c(&quot;hello&quot;).&lt;br/&gt;
Instead, I have to do V.c.call(&quot;hello&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;groovy&amp;gt; interface V { Closure c = &lt;/p&gt;
{ println it }
&lt;p&gt; }&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; V.c(&quot;hello&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; go&lt;br/&gt;
Caught: java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;br/&gt;
        at CommandLine.run(CommandLine.groovy:2)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
